          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "As a coalition of lawmakers tries to hold the billionaire Sackler family accountable for its role in the opioid crisis, Washington’s most powerful business lobby group has now jumped into the intensifying battle over whether courts can grant sweeping legal immunity to those accused of corporate crime.",
